  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2010_Solutions_2010s_page_001_27",
    "text": "We proceed now to the proof. Assume by way of contradiction that there exist a, b € G with a x b # 0. Put c = ax b = a*b, so that a,b, e are nonzero and linSay independents Vete be the id in element bad. exa=exb= exc=0. Since a, b, e span R3, ex* =0 for all * E R', so e = 0.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5562463351214004,
      0.5988372092038149,
      0.9229323288960062,
      0.7006448414276921
    ],
    "page": "exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2010_Solutions_2010s_page_001",
    "order": 22
