  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2010_Solutions_2010s_page_001_11",
    "text": "Define the function g : R → R by g(x) = f(x+ 1) f(x), and put c = g(0), d = f(0). For all x E R, 8' (x) = f(x + 1) - f(x) = 0, so g(x) = c identically, and f(x) = f(x+1) - f(x) = g(x) =c, so f(x) = cx+d identically as desired.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.12593986446362662,
      0.6046511626558496,
      0.4906015054724391,
      0.6758720930490922
    ],
    "page": "exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2010_Solutions_2010s_page_001",
    "order": 23
